By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Nigeria now has 53,727 confirmed cases with the 250 new infections recorded on Saturday as announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control. According to the report released via twitter handle, 41,314 patients have been discharged, with 1,011 lives lost to the coronavirus pandemic since the index case in February 27, 2020. Plateau state which has maintained the lead in the past three days recorded 69 infections while FCT and Lagos followed wih 41 and 21 cases respectively. Others are :   Delta and  Kaduna-14 each,  Bayelsa and  Enugu-13 each;  Ekiti-11;  Bauchi-9;  Ogun-8;  Edo and Oyo-7 each;  Rivers-6;  Adamawa and Osun -4 each; Nasarawa-3;  Ebonyi and Kwara-2 each; Gombe and Imo-1 each. See how the states stand: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria's COVID-19 cases crossed 50,000 on Wednesday as Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 593 new infections. This new recorded cases has brought to 50,488 the number of confirmed cases in the country. Announcing this yesterday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC)… August 20, 2020 In "Top Stories" Nigerian Government on Friday said 18-man team of Chinese medical experts will arrive the country in a few days to assist the country in its fight against coronavirus. “An 18-man team of Chinese medical experts including doctors, nurses and other medical advisers shall come along with the flight to assist… April 4, 2020 In "News" The Kaduna State Government has confirmed that 18 new cases of coronavirus disease have been recorded in the State. The Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, on Thursday announced that 339 new cases of the viral infection have been recorded in the country. Out of the 339 new cases confirmed,… May 22, 2020 In "News"